...is an implicit packet sequence number represented as uint32.
The packet sequence_number itself is not included in the packet
sent over the wire. The sequence_number is initialized to zero
for the first packet, and is incremented after every packet
(regargless of whether encryption or MAC is in use). It is never
reset (even if keys/algorithms are renegotiated later!). It wraps
around to zero after every 2^32 packets.
